                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2840.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-20T17:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 20, 1912—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Railroad destroyed 40 miles south of Guadalajara, and frequent revolutionary
                    rumors throughout State of Jalisco. Increase of <pb facs="0838" n="722"
                        xml:id="pg_722"/> local garrison urgent, and representations have to-day
                    been made to the Mexican Government. A well-known American resident on the
                    Isthmus of Tehauntepec reports a state of affairs there which may at any moment
                    result in a general uprising dangerous to life and property. This has been
                    informally brought to the attention of Minister for Foreign Affairs, as have
                    conditions in Oaxaca, where a general uprising is feared.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
